This is to allow trusting of the TLS certificate from clients:

1. Adds a new `get_tls_ca_certificate` FFI function
2. Adds a new set of self-signed certificates, alongside the CA (root certificate) that generated them

For example, in Go, I pass in a server config to the test function, that allows the test to configure the HTTP client with the dynamic port as well as get a handle to a pre-configured TLS setup:

```go
	var test = func(config v3.MockServerConfig) error {
		client := &http.Client{
			Transport: &http.Transport{
				TLSClientConfig: config.TLSConfig,
			},
		}
                // make the actual call
		// client.Do(...)
        }
```
